# Keep Docs Updated

After any code, config, CLI, or architecture change, update the relevant docs in the same turn before considering the work done.

## Doc map

| Doc | Update when |
|-----|-------------|
| `README.md` | User-facing usage, status, CLI examples, `pixi.toml` config shape, or high-level design highlights change |
| `docs/DESIGN.md` | Goals, pipeline, types, Pixi integration, asset matching, lockfile, CLI surface, or implementation phases change |

## Checklist

1. Identify what the change affects (behavior, API/CLI, config schema, architecture).
2. Update the matching sections so docs match the code — do not leave stale examples or outdated claims.
3. Prefer editing existing sections over appending duplicate content.
4. If the change is docs-only, skip this rule.

## Do not

- Ship code changes that contradict `README.md` or `docs/DESIGN.md`
- Add new docs files unless the existing ones cannot cover the change
- Mention this rule in commit messages or PR descriptions
